PhosR: analysis of FL83B and Hepa 1-6 insulin stimuation dataset

Di Xiao; Pengyi Yang

10 April, 2020

Description: This Rmarkdown file documents the imputation and downstream differential phosphorylation and signalling pathway enrichment analysis of the FL83B and Hepa 1-6 insulin stimuation dataset.

1 Data wrangling steps

library(PhosR)
load("./phospho_NB_raw.RData")

Extacting mouse cell line insulin stimulation data. Select columns that correspond to phosphosite quantification of FL83B and Hepa 1-6 cells in control and insulin stimulated conditions. After selecting the raw data from these columns transform the data using log2 and mark the missing values as NA.

phospho.cells.Ins <- as.matrix(log2(phospho.raw[,c(grep("FL83B_Control_\\d$", colnames(phospho.raw)), 
                                                   grep("FL83B_Ins_\\d$", colnames(phospho.raw)),
                                                   grep("Hepa1.6_Control_\\d$", colnames(phospho.raw)), 
                                                   grep("Hepa1.6_Ins_\\d$", colnames(phospho.raw)))]))
phospho.cells.Ins[is.infinite(phospho.cells.Ins)] <- NA

Extract the grouping information for biological replicates in each cell type and condition.

grps <- gsub("_\\d", "", colnames(phospho.cells.Ins))

2 Filtering of phosphosites

Select sites that have at least 50% quantification rate (q > 0.5) in one or more conditions

phospho.cells.Ins.filtered <- selectGrps(phospho.cells.Ins, grps, 0.5, n=1)
dim(phospho.cells.Ins)
## [1] 49617    24
dim(phospho.cells.Ins.filtered)
## [1] 17630    24

3 Imputation

3.1 Site- and condition-specific imputation

For each phosphosite in each condition, impute its missing values in that condition (if any) using site- and condition-specific imputation (scImpute) if the quantification rate in that condition is equal or greater than 50%.

set.seed(123)
cols <- rep(c("#ED4024", "#7FBF42", "#3F61AD", "#9B822F"), each=6)
phospho.cells.Ins.impute1 <- scImpute(phospho.cells.Ins.filtered, 0.5, grps)[,colnames(phospho.cells.Ins.filtered)]

3.2 Paired tail-based imputation

For each phosphosite, impute missing values with an estimated background value if we have 4 or more biological replicates quantified in insulin stimulated condition and 0 replicates quantified in the control condition.

phospho.cells.Ins.impute <- phospho.cells.Ins.impute1
# Impute data for FL83B in control using tail imputation approach
phospho.cells.Ins.impute[,1:6] <- ptImpute(phospho.cells.Ins.impute1[,7:12], 
                                           phospho.cells.Ins.impute1[,1:6], 4, 0, paired = FALSE)
## [1] "idx1: 371"
# Impute data for Hepa 1-6 in control using tail imputation aproach
phospho.cells.Ins.impute[,13:18] <- ptImpute(phospho.cells.Ins.impute1[,19:24], 
                                             phospho.cells.Ins.impute1[,13:18], 4, 0, paired = FALSE)
## [1] "idx1: 632"
# centring data across their median
phospho.cells.Ins.ms <- medianScaling(phospho.cells.Ins.impute, scale = FALSE)

3.3 Quantification plots

Barplot showing quantification rate before and after the above imputation procedure

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
plotQC(phospho.cells.Ins.filtered, labels=colnames(phospho.cells.Ins.filtered), panel = 1, cols = cols)
plotQC(phospho.cells.Ins.ms, labels=colnames(phospho.cells.Ins.ms), panel = 1, cols = cols)

Clustering of biological replicates before and after the above imputation procedure

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
plotQC(phospho.cells.Ins.filtered, labels=colnames(phospho.cells.Ins.filtered), panel = 2, cols = cols)
plotQC(phospho.cells.Ins.ms, labels=colnames(phospho.cells.Ins.ms), panel = 2, cols = cols)

4 Calling differentially phosphorylated sites

We use limma package for calling for differentially phosphorylated sites

library(limma)
# construct design matrix by group
f <- gsub("Intensity.", "", grps)
design <- model.matrix(~ f - 1)

4.1 Analysis of data before (without) imputation

Fitting a linear model to the phosphorylation level for each phosphosite.

# fit linear model for each phosphosite
fit <- lmFit(phospho.cells.Ins.filtered, design)
## Warning: Partial NA coefficients for 5649 probe(s)
# construct the constrast matrix corresponding to the FL83B and Hepa 1-6 in control.
contrast.matrix <- makeContrasts(fFL83B_Ins-fFL83B_Control, fHepa1.6_Ins-fHepa1.6_Control, levels=design)
# compute contrasts from linear model fit
fit2 <- contrasts.fit(fit, contrast.matrix)
# compute empirical bayes statistics from above linear model fit
fit2 <- eBayes(fit2)

Counting and visualise differentially phosphorylated sites for FL83B cells in control and insulin-simulated condition before imputation.

# Order the genes by how differentially they expressed 
FL83B.b.DE <- topTable(fit2, coef="fFL83B_Ins - fFL83B_Control", number = Inf)
plot(FL83B.b.DE[,"logFC"], -log10(FL83B.b.DE[,"P.Value"]))

# Identify genes which are significantly upregulated
sel <- which(FL83B.b.DE[,"adj.P.Val"] < 0.05 & FL83B.b.DE[,"logFC"] > 0)
length(sel)
## [1] 307
points(FL83B.b.DE[sel,"logFC"], -log10(FL83B.b.DE[sel,"P.Value"]), pch=16, col="red")

# Identify genes which are significantly downregulated
sel <- which(FL83B.b.DE[,"adj.P.Val"] < 0.05 & FL83B.b.DE[,"logFC"] < 0)
length(sel)
## [1] 556
points(FL83B.b.DE[sel,"logFC"], -log10(FL83B.b.DE[sel,"P.Value"]), pch=16, col="blue")

Counting and visualise differentially phosphorylated sites for Hepa 1-6 cells in control and insulin-simulated condition before imputation.

Hepa1.6.b.DE <- topTable(fit2, coef="fHepa1.6_Ins - fHepa1.6_Control", number = Inf)
plot(Hepa1.6.b.DE[,"logFC"], -log10(Hepa1.6.b.DE[,"P.Value"]))
sel <- which(Hepa1.6.b.DE[,"adj.P.Val"] < 0.05 & Hepa1.6.b.DE[,"logFC"] > 0)
length(sel)
## [1] 1409
points(Hepa1.6.b.DE[sel,"logFC"], -log10(Hepa1.6.b.DE[sel,"P.Value"]), pch=16, col="red")
sel <- which(Hepa1.6.b.DE[,"adj.P.Val"] < 0.05 & Hepa1.6.b.DE[,"logFC"] < 0)
length(sel)
## [1] 79
points(Hepa1.6.b.DE[sel,"logFC"], -log10(Hepa1.6.b.DE[sel,"P.Value"]), pch=16, col="blue")

4.2 Analysis of data after (with) imputation

Fitting a linear model to the phosphorylation level for each phosphosite.

fit <- lmFit(phospho.cells.Ins.ms, design)
## Warning: Partial NA coefficients for 5159 probe(s)
contrast.matrix <- makeContrasts(fFL83B_Ins-fFL83B_Control, fHepa1.6_Ins-fHepa1.6_Control, levels=design)
fit2 <- contrasts.fit(fit, contrast.matrix)
fit2 <- eBayes(fit2)

Counting and visualise differentially phosphorylated sites for FL83B cells in control and insulin-simulated condition after imputation.

FL83B.a.DE <- topTable(fit2, coef="fFL83B_Ins - fFL83B_Control", number = Inf)
plot(FL83B.a.DE[,"logFC"], -log10(FL83B.a.DE[,"P.Value"]))
sel <- which(FL83B.a.DE[,"adj.P.Val"] < 0.05 & FL83B.a.DE[,"logFC"] > 0)
length(sel)

sel <- which(FL83B.a.DE[,"adj.P.Val"] < 0.05 & FL83B.a.DE[,"logFC"] < 0)
length(sel)
## [1] 1218
points(FL83B.a.DE[sel,"logFC"], -log10(FL83B.a.DE[sel,"P.Value"]), pch=16, col="blue")

Counting and visualise differentially phosphorylated sites for Hepa 1-6 cells in control and insulin-simulated condition after imputation.

plot(Hepa1.6.a.DE[,"logFC"], -log10(Hepa1.6.a.DE[,"P.Value"]))

5 Performing signalling pathway enrichment analysis to compare data before and after imputation

5.1 Pathway enrichment analysis for FL83B cells in control and insulin-simulated conditions before imputation

# summarise phosphosite-level information to the gene level
FL83B.b.DE.FC <- FL83B.b.DE[,"logFC"]
id <- sapply(strsplit(rownames(FL83B.b.DE), "~"), function(x)toupper(x[2]))
FL83B.b.DE.gene <- phosCollapse(FL83B.b.DE.FC, id = id, stat = abs(FL83B.b.DE.FC), by = "max")

# perform pathway enrichment analysis
FL83B.before <- pathwayRankBasedEnrichment(FL83B.b.DE.gene[,1], annotation=Pathways.reactome, alter = "greater")

5.2 Pathway enrichment analysis for FL83B cells in control and insulin-simulated conditions after imputation

FL83B.a.DE.FC <- FL83B.a.DE[,"logFC"]
id <- sapply(strsplit(rownames(FL83B.a.DE), "~"), function(x)toupper(x[2]))
FL83B.a.DE.gene <- phosCollapse(FL83B.a.DE.FC, id = id, stat = abs(FL83B.a.DE.FC), by = "max")
FL83B.after <- pathwayRankBasedEnrichment(FL83B.a.DE.gene[,1], annotation=Pathways.reactome, alter = "greater")

5.3 Pathway enrichment analysis for Hepa1-6 cells in control and insulin-simulated conditions before imputation

Hepa1.6.b.DE.FC <- Hepa1.6.b.DE[,"logFC"]
id <- sapply(strsplit(rownames(Hepa1.6.b.DE), "~"), function(x)toupper(x[2]))
Hepa1.6.b.DE.gene <- phosCollapse(Hepa1.6.b.DE.FC, id = id, stat = abs(Hepa1.6.b.DE.FC), by = "max")
Hepa1.6.before <- pathwayRankBasedEnrichment(Hepa1.6.b.DE.gene[,1], annotation=Pathways.reactome, alter = "greater")

5.4 Pathway enrichment analysis for Hepa1-6 cells in control and insulin-simulated conditions after imputation

Hepa1.6.a.DE.FC <- Hepa1.6.a.DE[,"logFC"]
id <- sapply(strsplit(rownames(Hepa1.6.a.DE), "~"), function(x)toupper(x[2]))
Hepa1.6.a.DE.gene <- phosCollapse(Hepa1.6.a.DE.FC, id = id, stat = abs(Hepa1.6.a.DE.FC), by = "max")
Hepa1.6.after <- pathwayRankBasedEnrichment(Hepa1.6.a.DE.gene[,1], annotation=Pathways.reactome, alter = "greater")

5.5 Plot the comparison of pathway enrichment of FL83B before and after imputation.

sel <- intersect(rownames(FL83B.after)[1:10], rownames(FL83B.before)[1:10])[c(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)]
barplot(rbind(-log10(as.numeric(FL83B.before[sel,1])), -log10(as.numeric(FL83B.after[sel,1]))), beside = TRUE,
        names=sel, las=2, main="FL83B")

5.6 Plot the comparison of pathway enrichment of Hepa1-6 before and after imputation.

sel <- intersect(rownames(Hepa1.6.after)[1:10], rownames(Hepa1.6.before)[1:10])[c(1,2,3,5,6)]
barplot(rbind(-log10(as.numeric(Hepa1.6.before[sel,1])), -log10(as.numeric(Hepa1.6.after[sel,1]))), beside = TRUE,
        names=sel, las=2, main="Hepa 1-6")
